Date: 96-05, 1996,  
Pubnum: Memorandum COSOR  
Abstract: We show in a rather general framework that if the motion of an economy can be described by a set of autonomous (differential) equations and if the economy is aiming at sustainability, the value of the total stocks of capital should be constant over time. For the case where time enters the constraints explicitly we provide a modification of this rule. 
